menu "Trashboy"

config TRASHBOY_BT_SCAN_ENABLED
    bool "Enable Bluetooth keyboard scanning on boot"
    default y
    help
      When enabled (production default), the boot flow loops trying to
      auto-connect a paired Bluetooth HID keyboard and falls back to
      pairing-scan (devices_scan), then waits for the user to press ENTER
      on the splash screen to continue.

      Disable this for testing on hardware where no Bluetooth keyboard is
      paired or present: boot will skip both the scan loop and the splash
      ENTER-wait so it proceeds without user interaction.

config TRASHBOY_WIFI_USE_PRESET
    bool "Use preset Wi-Fi credentials instead of the interactive dialog"
    default n
    help
      When enabled, the Wi-Fi setup step at boot tries to connect to the
      SSID/password configured below before showing the on-device network
      picker. If the preset fails to connect, the normal interactive
      scan/pick/password dialog is used as a fallback.

      Intended for developer iteration so a board can boot straight onto
      a known test network without keyboard interaction. Credentials are
      compiled into the firmware image -- do not enable for shipped builds.

config TRASHBOY_WIFI_PRESET_SSID
    string "Preset Wi-Fi SSID"
    depends on TRASHBOY_WIFI_USE_PRESET
    default ""

config TRASHBOY_WIFI_PRESET_PASSWORD
    string "Preset Wi-Fi password"
    depends on TRASHBOY_WIFI_USE_PRESET
    default ""

config TRASHBOY_TOUCH_TEST_MODE
    bool "Boot into the GT911 touch test screen"
    default n
    help
      When enabled, the firmware boots straight into a self-contained test
      screen ("Touch Test" label, with a coloured circle painted at every
      touch press) and never reaches the normal BT / Wi-Fi / splash /
      RetroStore flow. Intended for bring-up of the touch stack on the
      Waveshare ESP32-S3-Touch-LCD-2.8B module (GT911 over I2C, TP_INT on
      GPIO 16, TP_RST via TCA9554 EXIO2).

endmenu
